					</li>
				</ul>
			</header>

			<div class="about-content">
				<section aria-labelledby="about-work">
					<h2 id="about-work">What I do</h2>
					<p>I work at the intersection of software development, product, technology leadership, and operations. The consistent thread across my career has been using technology to solve real operational problems—translating business needs into software, building and leading teams, and creating systems that work in practice.</p>
					<p>I currently serve as CTO at ShramIN Jobs, where I lead the development and evolution of the platform while working closely with operations. My domain experience spans employment, skilling, agriculture, rural supply chains, financial inclusion, and livelihoods.</p>
				</section>

				<section aria-labelledby="about-career">
					<h2 id="about-career">Career</h2>
					<ol class="career-list">
						<li>
							<h3>ShramIN Jobs</h3>
							<p class="career-role">CTO · 2021–present</p>
							<p>Leading the development and continuous improvement of the employment platform, connecting product and technology decisions with the needs of job seekers, employers, and operations teams.</p>
						</li>
						<li>
							<h3>AgriDost</h3>
							<p class="career-role">Co-founder and CTO · 2017–2021</p>
							<p>Shaped the product and technology strategy for solutions supporting farmers with agricultural productivity, digital adoption, and financial literacy.</p>
						</li>
						<li>
							<h3>Anudip Foundation</h3>
							<p class="career-role">Assistant General Manager, Skilling Operations · 2016–2017</p>
							<p>Led the delivery and impact measurement of market-aligned software skills programs conducted with corporate partners across India.</p>
						</li>
						<li>
							<h3>Drishtee</h3>
							<p class="career-role">Technology, process, programs, and operations leadership · 2007–2016</p>
							<p>Progressed through roles in IT, business process design, skill-development programs, financial inclusion, rural supply chains, and regional operations.</p>
						</li>
						<li>
							<h3>Cyber Infodev</h3>
							<p class="career-role">Assistant Manager, Technical · 2006–2007</p>
							<p>Led a software team delivering systems for e-governance projects.</p>
						</li>
						<li>
							<h3>Drishtee Foundation</h3>
							<p class="career-role">Senior Programmer · 2005–2006</p>
							<p>Worked as part of the in-house software development team at the start of my professional career.</p>
						</li>
					</ol>
				</section>

				<section aria-labelledby="about-focus">
					<h2 id="about-focus">Areas of experience</h2>
					<ul>
						<li>Software and product development</li>
						<li>Technology and operations leadership</li>
						<li>Skilling, employment, and livelihoods</li>
						<li>Agriculture and rural supply chains</li>
						<li>Financial inclusion</li>
						<li>Process design and organizational systems</li>
					</ul>
				</section>

				<section aria-labelledby="about-education">
					<h2 id="about-education">Education</h2>
					<ul>
						<li>Master of Computer Applications, Madurai Kamaraj University</li>
						<li>Post Graduate Diploma in Computer Applications, University of Delhi</li>
						<li>Bachelor of Commerce, Chaudhary Charan Singh University</li>
					</ul>
				</section>

				<section aria-labelledby="about-beyond">
					<h2 id="about-beyond">Beyond work</h2>
					<p>I build small open-source products and write about technology, productivity, products, and the systems we use to get work done. Outside that, I enjoy travel, reading about business and current affairs, and listening to music.</p>
					<p>I speak Hindi and English, along with some Bengali and Odia.</p>
				</section>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>
</SiteLayout>
